# Privacy Policy — Only the Best

**Last updated:** June 26, 2026  
**Developer:** Alexandr Garlock

## Overview

Only the Best is a restaurant discovery app. We are committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains what data the app collects, how it is used, and with whom it is shared.

## Data We Collect

### Location
We collect your precise location to search for top-rated restaurants near you. Location data is sent to the Google Places API solely to fulfill search requests and is not stored on our servers (we have no servers). You can deny location access at any time in iOS Settings.

### Sign In with Apple
We use Sign In with Apple for authentication. We receive only the minimal information Apple provides (a private user identifier). This identifier is stored locally on your device only, to track your free trial period. It is never transmitted to any external server.

### Usage Data
We store search counts and subscription status locally on your device using iOS standard storage (UserDefaults and Keychain). This data never leaves your device.

## Advertising

The free tier of Only the Best displays ads provided by **Google AdMob**. AdMob may collect device identifiers and usage data to serve personalized ads, subject to your App Tracking Transparency (ATT) choice when prompted. If you deny tracking, non-personalized ads are shown instead.

For AdMob's privacy practices, see: https://policies.google.com/privacy

## Subscriptions

Plus and Pro subscriptions are processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We do not collect or store your payment information. Subscription management is handled through your Apple ID.

